shouldn't worry at all.

03:11.224 --> 03:13.898
You have every reason
to expect a healthy child.

03:14.060 --> 03:16.666
In fact, if you'd like, you can
provide your sample today.

03:17.363 --> 03:20.071
Today?
Like, today, today?

03:20.133 --> 03:21.407
This today?
Well, yes.

03:21.467 --> 03:23.970
I mean, the timing is right according
to Ann's ovulation schedule.

03:24.037 --> 03:26.779
Unless there's a reason you'd
like to wait till next month.

03:26.906 --> 03:28.146
(sums)

03:28.408 --> 03:29.887
No.

03:29.943 --> 03:31.251
None.

03:31.644 --> 03:33.453
One other question.
Completely off topic.

03:33.513 --> 03:36.722
Would I be providing
this sample... Today?

03:38.418 --> 03:40.625
Here I am thinking
about how fast

03:40.687 --> 03:42.860
my first year in
city council has gone,

03:42.922 --> 03:47.234
and Jerry has had 40 years whiz past
him with nothing to show for it.

03:47.293 --> 03:48.772
This is everything
in his file,

03:48.861 --> 03:51.364
a handicapped parking sticker
from when he got gout,

03:51.431 --> 03:54.935
a Parks and Rec golf cart
driving exam which he failed,

03:55.034 --> 03:57.014
a scathing
performance review.

03:57.170 --> 03:59.309
I mean, why would
anyone be so mean?

03:59.606 --> 04:00.710
Oh, wait. I wrote this.

04:01.174 --> 04:02.244
I stand by it.

04:02.308 --> 04:03.912
Well, Jerry was
never really the type

04:04.043 --> 04:07.217
to rise above
mediocrity or to it.

04:07.347 --> 04:09.122
That's what I thought,
but when he started,

04:09.249 --> 04:11.024
he had a lot of
dreams and goals.

04:11.084 --> 04:13.564
I mean, look at his
original entry paperwork.

04:13.720 --> 04:17.361
He wanted to meet the mayor,
have a building named after him.

04:17.423 --> 04:20.632
I just can't let Jerry leave here with
nothing and go home to an empty life.

04:20.726 --> 04:23.799
Well, I'll help with anything.
Just promise we'll do it quickly.

04:23.863 --> 04:25.672
I'm making us a mac
and cheese pizza for...

04:25.732 --> 04:27.234
Mac and cheese pizza?
Yeah.

04:27.300 --> 04:28.643
You're making that?
Yeah.

04:28.735 --> 04:29.736
(GASPS)

04:31.971 --> 04:34.508
Torturing Jerry was my
favorite thing in the world.

04:34.874 --> 04:36.217
After making out
with you.

04:36.276 --> 04:38.347
Remember when we did both
at the same time?

04:38.411 --> 04:40.288
It made him
so uncomfortable.

04:40.346 --> 04:41.347
(BOTH LAUGHING)

04:41.447 --> 04:44.121
This is a sad day. Who are
we gonna make fun of now?

04:44.183 --> 04:45.184
RON: No need to worry.

04:45.251 --> 04:47.788
Every place I've ever worked
in has had a "Jerry."

04:47.854 --> 04:48.992
When one Jerry leaves,

04:49.055 --> 04:52.628
the office naturally selects
a new Jerry to fill that role.

04:52.692 --> 04:55.536
It's Social Darwinism.
The strong prey on the weak.

04:55.762 --> 04:59.539
Soon, one of you
will be ridiculed mercilessly.

04:59.832 --> 05:01.607
Ha! Nature.

05:04.604 --> 05:06.140
Okay.
My transfer was approved.

05:06.205 --> 05:09.550
So starting now, lam an employee
of the County Health Board.

05:09.609 --> 05:10.883
You are no longer
my boss,

05:10.943 --> 05:12.854
and we can have a baby without
it being a conflict of interest.

05:12.912 --> 05:14.186
Clear sailing.

05:14.247 --> 05:16.386
Goodbye, Ann Perkins,
my excellent employee.

05:16.716 --> 05:19.162
Hello, Ann Perkins,
my fallopian princess.

05:19.419 --> 05:20.864
So here's the drill.

05:21.020 --> 05:22.260
Make a deposit in here.

05:22.322 --> 05:24.233
If you fill it up all the way,
you get on the board.

05:25.925 --> 05:27.871
