spin it in the centrifuge,

05:27.927 --> 05:29.201
and prepare it
for fertilization.

05:29.262 --> 05:30.434
Sounds romantic.

05:31.831 --> 05:33.708
I guess it's go time.
Go time!

05:34.434 --> 05:36.072
Wait, what am I doing?
I don't go with you.

05:36.135 --> 05:40.049
Oh, no, no. I go in alone with this
pornographic disc and do it myself.

05:40.106 --> 05:41.346
And you stay out here

05:41.407 --> 05:42.909
and try not to think about
what I'm doing in there.

05:42.975 --> 05:44.545
And I try not to think
about you waiting out here

05:44.610 --> 05:45.953
trying not to
think about me.

05:46.212 --> 05:47.452
Should I think about you?

05:48.181 --> 05:49.387
This is so weird.

05:49.449 --> 05:51.486
Chris, we don't
have to do this today.

05:51.851 --> 05:55.924
This was totally just sprung on us.
Let's just take a moment.

05:55.988 --> 05:58.559
There's so many
pamphlets to look at.

05:58.624 --> 06:02.265
Yes, we do have very important
pamphlet reading to do.

06:02.495 --> 06:04.338
Excellent idea,
Ann Perkins.

06:05.331 --> 06:06.605
Do I keep this?

06:07.100 --> 06:10.343
I don't know. It feels wrong to
leave it here. Give it to me.

06:12.972 --> 06:14.007
I panicked. Run!

06:17.110 --> 06:19.920
Here are the last
of the Animal Control reports.

06:23.015 --> 06:24.392
What are you doing,
weirdo?

06:24.617 --> 06:26.824
Just trying not
to spill anything.

06:26.986 --> 06:29.728
I believe Leslie said
to organize these by year.

06:30.022 --> 06:32.832
Way ahead of you.
I made two pile files.

06:33.159 --> 06:34.160
(DONNA LAUGHS)

06:34.427 --> 06:37.465
Pilo fibles. Filo pilos.

06:37.563 --> 06:39.133
Filo pilos?
That's not right.

06:39.198 --> 06:40.438
Are you broken?
(APRIL LAUGHS)

06:40.566 --> 06:42.409
No, everything's fine.
(RON LAUGHS)

06:42.502 --> 06:44.607
Well, I guess that settles
who the new Jerry is.

06:44.670 --> 06:47.082
No, it doesn't!
I barely even said it wrong.

06:47.140 --> 06:48.710
Said it wrong.
Stop it!

06:48.875 --> 06:50.149
(ALL LAUGH)

06:51.344 --> 06:52.687
This is how it begins.

06:53.112 --> 06:54.489
The next "Jerry."

06:54.614 --> 06:57.060
One screwed-up sentence,
and 30 years later,

06:57.116 --> 06:58.959
I'm wearing
aquamarine sweater vests

06:59.018 --> 07:02.693
and listening to Bonnie Raitt and
The <i>Da Vinci Code</i> on my iPod.

07:05.391 --> 07:06.563
(ALL LAUGH)

07:06.859 --> 07:07.963
It's already started.

07:10.263 --> 07:12.539
Believe it or not,
Jerry, you were young once.

07:12.598 --> 07:13.872
Young and full of dreams.

07:13.933 --> 07:15.640
(LAUGHS) I forgot I wrote
all this.

07:15.701 --> 07:18.807
And as unrealistic and
absurd as those goals were,

07:18.905 --> 07:21.511
we are not letting you retire
until we help you achieve them.

07:22.508 --> 07:24.351
So let's see
what's first.

07:24.410 --> 07:27.687
"Eat in city council private
dining room." That we can achieve.

07:27.947 --> 07:29.927
Right now?
Sure. Let's go.

07:30.349 --> 07:31.487
Authorized personnel only.

07:31.617 --> 07:32.755
Oh, they're with me.

07:32.819 --> 07:35.857
City Councilor Leslie Knope,
clearance level four.

07:35.922 --> 07:38.300
Guests are only
allowed on Wednesdays.

07:38.357 --> 07:40.394
And we don't have
clearance levels.

07:40.460 --> 07:42.997
I know, but shouldn't we?
I mean, it sounds so cool.

07:43.062 --> 07:45.042
Anyway, we just need to get
in there real quick

07:45.097 --> 07:46.701
and maybe take a picture.

07:46.766 --> 07:50.236
He's retiring as a City Hall
employee after 41 years,

07:50.303 --> 07:51.839
and it was his dream
to eat here.

07:51.904 --> 07:53.315
His dream? Really?

07:54.207 --> 07:55.379
Still no.

07:55.441 --> 07:56.442
It's okay, Leslie.
Come on.

07:56.509 --> 07:57.544
But thank you.
Thank you for trying.

07:57.610 --> 07:59.419
No, no, no, no, no. I promised
you an executive meal

07:59.479 --> 08:00.617
and you're gonna
get one.

08:00.680 --> 08:02.660
Ben. Okay.

08:02.715 --> 08:05.093
I'm gonna go in there
and take a picture with Jerry.

08:05.218 --> 08:06.856
I put my arm around nothing.

08:06.919 --> 08:09.160
And then you photoshop
him in later, okay?

08:12.758 --> 08:14.396
Congratulations
on your retirement.

08:14.527 --> 08:16.200
Aw, thank you.

08:17.396 --> 08:20.468
One, three,
seven, two, five, nine.

08:21.400 --> 08:23.402
Sudoku is easy.

