I'm so sorry

10:11.043 --> 10:13.523
that those Serbian mobsters shoved
you out of that helicopter.

10:13.579 --> 10:14.580
You deserve better.

10:14.981 --> 10:17.052
Okay, you tried,
but I took a day off

10:17.116 --> 10:20.791
to spend with you, not with you
and Jerry and a dead mayor.

10:20.886 --> 10:22.331
Can we please
just call it a day?

10:22.388 --> 10:24.527
No, we can't because
in a few short years,

10:24.590 --> 10:26.035
we're gonna be
visiting Jerry here,

10:26.092 --> 10:27.298
and he will have
achieved nothing.

10:27.560 --> 10:28.595
Is that what you want?

10:28.661 --> 10:30.038
No.
Okay, then.

10:30.129 --> 10:31.506
It's really been
nice to meet you.

10:32.398 --> 10:33.706
Okay, Jerry, let's go.
(CLEARS THROAT) Whoo.

10:34.166 --> 10:36.112
Ron-fire of the Vanities.

10:36.235 --> 10:37.509
Filo Pilo.

10:37.603 --> 10:38.707
(SIGHS)
Are you kidding me?

10:39.138 --> 10:41.175
Listen, now that
Jerry's gone,

10:41.240 --> 10:42.583
we need to hire someone
to pick up the slack.

10:42.642 --> 10:43.985
A new person in the office?

10:44.043 --> 10:45.886
Not a person. An intern.

10:46.445 --> 10:48.482
Why on earth
would I get an intern?

10:48.581 --> 10:51.494
Interns cost nothing
to the taxpayer.

10:51.784 --> 10:54.287
And more importantly, they're
usually stupid and terrible.

10:54.387 --> 10:56.890
So they get no work done. It's like
a Jerry you don't have to pay.

10:56.956 --> 10:59.061
Damn, son. That is
one compelling argument.

10:59.825 --> 11:01.065
Keep it up, Filo.

11:01.127 --> 11:03.129
We may destroy this government
one day after all.

11:05.965 --> 11:08.377
These pamphlets
are fascinating.

11:08.434 --> 11:10.812
It says here that some men
gain "sympathy weight"

11:10.870 --> 11:12.110
